            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, season your <strong>salmon fillet[s] </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Lay the <strong>salmon</strong> over the <strong>spinach & tomato orzo </strong>and cook, covered, for 8-10 min further or until the salmon is cooked through – this is your <strong>creamy salmon florentine</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily!</p>",
